\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5.2}{\ignorespaces Areas of phase-space regions have the units of action. Quantization of action implies quantization of phase-space area. (a) The smallest area in phase space is limited by the fundamental quantum of action $h$ -- Planck's constant. (b) Area of the ellipsis inside the path of harmonic oscillator is proportional to its energy. Quantization of area leads to the quantization of energy of harmonic oscillator.}}{157}{figure.caption.69}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:phaseSpaceQuantum}{{5.2}{157}{Areas of phase-space regions have the units of action. Quantization of action implies quantization of phase-space area. (a) The smallest area in phase space is limited by the fundamental quantum of action $h$ -- Planck's constant. (b) Area of the ellipsis inside the path of harmonic oscillator is proportional to its energy. Quantization of area leads to the quantization of energy of harmonic oscillator}{figure.caption.69}{}}
